{
  "stem": "22047.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It turns out that all of these major camps, like Dachau and Auschwitz and Belsen-Bergen, and-- all of those had supplemental camps.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Dachau had some 110 supplemental camps that had smaller amounts of prisoners there, mostly work details in the local areas that needed-- like in ammunition-producing factories and had these small camps that had a few hundred folks.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But Dachau itself had thousands-- thousands.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And as I said, that, you know, a young 20-year-old has never even imagined anything like this.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How-- how could this be?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How-- how in the world could people be treated this way?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How is it possible?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And to have the-- the-- the revolting and shocking and gut-wrenching feeling come over us to see something like that.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, after a time, you know, many of the prisoners-- we talked with them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and we-- we tried to tell them in-- in our broken German-- a lot of them-- most of them were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But there were a lot of other nationalities there, too.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were some Russian and Polish and French, all kinds of nationalities in this camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was able to speak some German, so I was able to converse somewhat.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the Belgian officer I was with spoke quite good German and French and Belgian.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And [LAUGHS] he was able to translate for me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I tried to tell the people that I talked to through him that we were there as liberators, although we had to keep them in there.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Please understand that we're not going to keep you in here forever.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we're not going to treat you like the Germans did.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
